From 79bbbdb366388dde14ae1ffc0b9351ceca44ba36 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Govinda Upadhyay <govinda.upadhyay@sipradi.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 11:34:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] fix: cascade link save, api error handling, perf sample
 with location+sector

- /api/cascade POST: replaced broken stub (wrong column names, silent
  try/except) with full implementation. Table now uses correct columns:
  parent_emp_id, parent_cp_id, child_emp_id, child_mp_id. Auto-creates
  child MP from the parent CP when left blank. GET returns enriched
  links with employee/CP/MP display names.

- api helper (index.html): checks Content-Type before .json() so Flask
  HTML error pages produce a readable toast (Server HTTP 500) instead
  of the cryptic 'Unexpected token < <!doctype' crash.

- Sample_Performance.csv now includes Sector_Code and Location_Code
  columns pulled from live DB, so the download matches what import
  actually expects.

- perf table migration: adds location_code and sector_code columns to
  existing DBs. Import route reads both columns from CSV and auto-
  derives sector from employee dept when not supplied.
