From cc3cb53a8c1501cc57397340914c2c9ebd98fc26 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Govinda Upadhyay <govinda.upadhyay@sipradi.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 05:57:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] fix: sector edit - modal error surfacing, staff count,
 code sync
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

3 bugs fixed:

Bug A - Silent save failures on all modals:
  openModal attached onclick=fn with no error handling. When api.put()
  threw (strict api._json raises on non-2xx), the error was swallowed
  silently — modal stayed open, appeared frozen/uneditable.
  Fix: every modal action button now wrapped in async try/catch that
  shows a toast with the actual error message.

Bug B - Sector cards showed 0 staff for all seeded sectors:
  renderSectors grouped by empsBySector[s.name] e.g. 'Head of Department'
  but employees store dept=s.code e.g. 'HOD'. All sector cards showed
  zero staff even with employees assigned.
  Fix: index by s.code and also pick up multi-sector employees via
  their sector_ids[] junction array.

Bug C - Sector PUT crashed with KeyError on missing code:
  d['code'] raised KeyError if code was blank. No fallback.
  Also: renaming a sector code did not update employees.dept.
  Fix: use d.get('code') with auto-derive from name, and sync
  employees.dept across all affected rows when code changes.
---
